node.text:
TODAAYYYY IS THE DAY!! @silk_canada #Ad HAS CHALLENGED ME TO TRY INTERMITTENT VEGANING AND IF YOU DON'T KNOW IT, IT'S AS SIMPLE AS ADDING IN MORE PLANT BASED FOODS INTO YOUR DAY TO DAY DIET, REPLACING SOME OF THE MEAT OR DAIRY YOU HAVE IN A DISH!

SINCE I LOVE THE FLAVOUR OF THE GOOD OL’ ORIGINAL SILK + THEIR COCONUT WHIP, I'VE DECIDED TO MAKE ONE OF MY FAVOURITE DESSERTS VEGAN: RICE PUDDING WITH STEWED MEDJOOL DATES!! TRUST ME, THE @silk_canada VERSION IS JUST AS DELICIOUS.  TAKE THE CHALLENGE AND LET ME KNOW WHAT YOU MAKE! #IntermittentVeganing #SilkCanada #GoodForYou

INGREDIENTS:
1 cup Arborio rice
3 cups Silk Original Soy Milk
1/2 cup red wine
1/2 cinnamon stick
3 cloves
3/4 cup maple syrup
1 cup pitted medjool dates (Add more as desired)
1 carton SILK whipping cream

node.title: VEGAN RICE PUDDING WITH STEWED MEDJOOL DATES
